============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     GAN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Generator vs discriminator adversarial training
Year:        2014
Researchers: Ian Goodfellow et al.
Applications:Image synthesis, deepfakes, augmentation
Related:     Mode collapse, discriminator, generator

Concept:     Transfer Learning
Category:    Technique
Definition:  Reuses pre-trained model weights for new related tasks
Year:        2009
Researchers: Pan and Yang survey
Applications:Fine-tuning LLMs, computer vision
Related:     Pre-training, fine-tuning, domain adaptation

Concept:     Attention Mechanism
Category:    Mechanism
Definition:  Learns to focus on relevant input parts for each output
Year:        2015
Researchers: Bahdanau et al.
Applications:Machine translation, NLP, summarization
Related:     Self-attention, multi-head, cross-attention

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Smallpox
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Variola
Transmission:Respiratory, contact
Symptoms:    Pockmarks, fever
Treatment:   Eradicated (1980)
Deaths/yr:   EradicatedM
Vaccine:     Yes
Discovered:  Antiquity

Disease:     Cancer
Type:        Cellular
Pathogen:    Various causes
Transmission:Non-communicable
Symptoms:    Lumps, weight loss, fatigue
Treatment:   Chemo, surgery, immunotherapy
Deaths/yr:   10.0M
Vaccine:     Some (HPV, Hep B vaccines)
Discovered:  Ancient

Disease:     Hepatitis B
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HBV
Transmission:Blood, sexual contact
Symptoms:    Often asymptomatic; jaundice
Treatment:   Antivirals (tenofovir)
Deaths/yr:   0.82M
Vaccine:     Yes (highly effective)
Discovered:  1965

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

Concept:    Central Bank
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government institution managing currency, money supply, interest rates
Formula:    Taylor Rule for interest rates
Economist:  John Taylor
Example:    US Federal Reserve raised rates to 5.25% in 2023 to fight inflation

